1
00:00:01,000 --> 00:00:04,000
Hi, have you been to Willowbrook before?

2
00:00:04,200 --> 00:00:07,500
No, this is my first time here. It's such a charming town.

3
00:00:07,700 --> 00:00:10,500
It really is. The people are friendly, and the scenery is beautiful.

4
00:00:10,700 --> 00:00:13,800
I can see that. What do you recommend I do while I’m here?

5
00:00:14,000 --> 00:00:17,000
Definitely visit the library. It's small but full of history.

6
00:00:17,200 --> 00:00:20,500
A library? That sounds peaceful. Do many visitors go there?

7
00:00:20,700 --> 00:00:23,000
Not a lot, but it’s a hidden gem. The librarian, Amelia, knows all the stories.

8
00:00:23,200 --> 00:00:26,000
Sounds like a great person to meet. I love hearing local stories.

9
00:00:26,200 --> 00:00:29,000
Exactly. Plus, the town square has a market every Saturday.

10
00:00:29,200 --> 00:00:32,000
Oh, I love markets. Fresh food and crafts are the best.

11
00:00:32,200 --> 00:00:35,000
You’ll find plenty there — fruits, veggies, homemade bread, even pottery.

12
00:00:35,200 --> 00:00:38,000
That’s wonderful. I want to try everything!

13
00:00:38,200 --> 00:00:41,000
Don’t forget to stroll by the river too. It’s especially beautiful at sunset.

14
00:00:41,200 --> 00:00:44,000
I will. Quiet nature walks are my favorite.

15
00:00:44,200 --> 00:00:47,000
There’s also a local café near the fountain. Their coffee is amazing.

16
00:00:47,200 --> 00:00:50,000
Coffee and a good book at the library — sounds perfect.

17
00:00:50,200 --> 00:00:53,000
It really is. I think you’ll love Willowbrook.

18
00:00:53,200 --> 00:00:56,000
Thanks for the tips. I’m excited to explore!

19
00:00:56,200 --> 00:00:59,000
Enjoy your visit. If you want, I can show you around sometime.

20
00:00:59,200 --> 00:01:02,000
That would be great, thanks! I appreciate it.

